This Porsche 997 911 Carrera 4S got away, but there are more like it here.

15k-Mile 2009 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S Coupe 6-Speed

USA
Sold for USD $105,000 on 12/22/2565Comments

This 2009 Porsche 911 Carrera 4S coupe remained with the original owner in California until 2023 and now has 15k miles. The car is powered by a 3.8-liter flat-six that drives all four wheels through a six-speed manual transaxle and is finished in Basalt Black Metallic over black leather. Equipment includes the Sport Chrono Package Plus, bi-xenon headlights, a sunroof, gray Porsche-script bodyside graphics, 19â BBS wheels, PCM with navigation, heated front seats, a Bose sound system, a CD player, and automatic climate control. This 997.2 C4S coupe is now offered with the ownerâs manual, service records, a clean Carfax report, and a clean Georgia title in the sellerâs name.

The 997 Carrera 4S features wider rear bodywork, and a reflective strip between the taillights when compared to the standard Carrera. This example is finished in Basalt Black Metallic (C9Z) with gray Porsche-script bodyside graphics. Additional equipment includes bi-xenon headlights, integrated fog lights, chrome-finished headlight washers, a sunroof, a speed-activated rear spoiler, black decklid badging, and quad exhaust outlets.

The 19â BBS wheels are mounted with 235/35 front and 305/30 rear Michelin Pilot Sport 4S tires that show 2022 and 2023 date codes. The car is equipped with Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and Porsche Stability Management (PSM).

The cabin features heated front sport seats upholstered in black leather, which extends to the dashboard and door panels. Interior amenities include PCM with navigation, a Bose sound system, a CD player, automatic climate control, and cruise control.

The leather-wrapped steering wheel frames a central tachometer and a 200-mph speedometer as well as gauges for oil temperature, oil pressure, coolant temperature, and fuel level. The optional Sport Chrono Package Plus added a stopwatch atop the dashboard. The digital odometer indicates 15k miles, approximately 2,400 of which were added under current ownership.

The 3.8-liter flat-six features VarioCam Plus variable valve timing for a factory rating of 385 horsepower and 310 lb-ft of torque. The front end control module was replaced in July 2019, and the spark plugs, engine air filter, and pollen filter were replaced in March 2023. An oil change was performed in September 2025.

Power is routed to all four wheels via a six-speed manual transaxle.
